
                        Section 2 - Notes
                        SHELL Instruction

1.  Dockerfile without SHELL instruction.

    $ cat Dockerfile
    FROM ubuntu:trusty
    CMD sleep 60

2.  Build image.

    $ docker build -t sc . 

3.  Run detached shell container.

    $ docker run -d --name shell sc 

4.  Look at shell used by container.

    $ docker ps -l
    CONTAINER ID   IMAGE          COMMAND          
    882b6e257c4f    sc     "/bin/sh -c 'sleep 60'"

    Note that default shell is /bin/sh.
    
5.  Dockerfile with SHELL instruction.

    $ cat Dockerfile
    FROM ubuntu:trusty
    SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
    CMD sleep 60

6.  Remove old detached shell container

    $ docker container rm shell

7.  Build image and detached shell container.

    $ docker build -t sc . 
    $ docker run -d --name shell sc 

8.  Look at shell used by container.

    $ docker ps -l
    CONTAINER ID   IMAGE        COMMAND             
    a1a7fcf5975f    sc    "/bin/bash -c 'sleep 60'"

    Note that default shell is now /bin/bash.
